### Step 1: Login as Admin (use seeded credentials)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/authentication/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "abdelrhmanali2119@gmail.com",
  "password": "Abdo@888"
}

### Step 2: Create Instructor Account (using admin token from Step 1)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/admin/instructors
Authorization: Bearer {{your_admin_token_here}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "instructor1@test.com",
  "firstName": "Test",
  "lastName": "Instructor",
  "password": "Instructor@123",
  "phoneNumber": "+1234567890"
}

### Step 3: Login as Instructor
POST http://localhost:5000/api/authentication/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "instructor1@test.com",
  "password": "Instructor@123"
}

### Step 4: Create Course with Your Data (using instructor token from Step 3)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/instructor/courses
Authorization: Bearer {{your_instructor_token_here}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "test1",
  "description": "test1",
  "thumbnailUrl": "https://example.com/thumbnail.jpg",
  "price": 100,
  "isFree": true,
  "estimatedDurationMinutes": 120,
  "category": "Programming",
  "level": "Beginner",
  "requirements": "Basic computer skills",
  "learningObjectives": "Learn the fundamentals"
}

### Step 5: Get All Courses Created by Instructor
GET http://localhost:5000/api/instructor/courses?pageIndex=1&pageSize=10
Authorization: Bearer {{your_instructor_token_here}}

### Step 6: Publish the Course
PATCH http://localhost:5000/api/instructor/courses/{{course_id}}/publish
Authorization: Bearer {{your_instructor_token_here}}
